        <hr noshade size="1">
        
        <font color="white" face="Verdana" size="2"> Ok, so with focus items, hp and int/mana gear, I am doing great, but I am having trouble with letting go of the notion that I need 80-100 mana and hp to engage things.</P><P>I have found that I can fight and do well, with never really going about 60 mana, but part of that is that i can still tank.</P><P>Generally, I run up to 60 mana, then leach/dot it down to 40-ish, and tank.</P><P>I run pact almost 24x7 to help it get back to 60 asap.</P><P>I was wondering if I should be a little "looser" and run closer to oom to pull faster, or even run at very low hp totals, instead of waiting for 60-80 hp.</P><P>I am curious tactically how this will play out with my 8 for 4 mana regen at level 20</P><P>My only other "caster" type char was a 35 druid, and I never dreamt of starting a fight lower than 60, usuually preffing 80 or fm, due to having no self mana regen.</P><P>Any ideas appreciated.</P><P>Noct<BR>14th Necromancer Chomedome of Ayonae Ro</font></td>

