         in my opinion...</P><P>always hang onto enough for a tap, root, FD, HS, fear, or whatever else you keep ready to save yer arse in case the mob gets lucky...</P><P>Lately, I've started to get more into Root-Rot, as opposed to Fear-kiting...guess it's cause I can bring the target to it's future final resting place, and med while it dies....not worrying about fear breaking, pet gettin whooped, etc.  (I have yet to be smacked by a mob that breaks root, so long as I get a darkness on it...plenty of time to refresh root while it shuffles over to you)</P><P>not sure if I answered your question, hehe  :)</P><P>Nikomya Xh'ree<BR>Bone Igniter (44 finally, yay :p)<BR>Cestus Dei-Veeshan</P><P>Edited by - Nikomya on 06/10/2002  12:07:45<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
