        <hr noshade size="2" color="#545A7D">
        
         Start your pulls at FM with lich on. Try to gage how much mana and HP you have at the end of the fight. Fromthen on, you know about how much mana the fight will take, so you know what you need at the end od the fight to keep going. </P><P>I personally always like to keep enough mana for a root FD , HS or gate in reserve at all times. i also wont pull below 40%hp unless it is a "safer" spot. I usually try to lifetap the mob a few times to get myself of 50% hp if i have the mana to spare.</P><P>hope that helps.</P><P><BR>taysir</P><P> <a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
