         It always totally depends on what I am fighting.  If I know that I need 2 blue of mana to kill something and stay safe with resists and such and I am at 40% life from liching, I'll go pull something at 3 blue of mana.  Vex takes arround a blue of mana and heals me about 2 red of health with lich on.  Then I end up at 80% health and 40% mana with a 1k DoT on the mob.  Sometimes I pull as long as I have barely enough mana to stick a splurt, dark and root.  By the time dark/splurt wears off, I have enough mana for another.  I only do that if the mobs I am fighting have very bad resists though.  If crap I am fighting is difficult and I need to kill them to get 'em out of the way or because they have gear I want or just because I want to see if I can kill them, I usualy wait for full health full mana just to be safe.</P><P>100% depends on what you're fighting.  If you're fighting something new, always go in full health full mana.  See how hard they are.  What their resists are, how much health they have and how hard they hit.  Then, decide what's a safe mana/health level to go in at.</P><P><A href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=26159">Reegor</A> Mortees<BR>scaled Warlock<a href="#top"><img src="icon_go_up.gif" height="15" width="15" border="0" align="right" alt="Go to Top of Page"></a></font></td>
